# Drizzle Database

All database interactions must go through Drizzle ORM using this project's schema and query APIs.

## Key files

- Client: [src/db/index.ts](mdc:src/db/index.ts) — import `db` from here
- Schema: [src/db/schema.ts](mdc:src/db/schema.ts) — table and relation definitions
- Migrations: [drizzle.config.ts](mdc:drizzle.config.ts) and `drizzle/` output

## Required patterns

- Import the shared client: `import { db } from "@/src/db"`
- Import tables from schema: `import { decksTable, cardsTable } from "@/src/db/schema"`
- Use Drizzle query builders (`select`, `insert`, `update`, `delete`) and operators from `drizzle-orm` (`eq`, `and`, `or`, etc.)

```typescript
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";
import { db } from "@/src/db";
import { cardsTable, decksTable } from "@/src/db/schema";

const decks = await db.select().from(decksTable).where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));

const [deck] = await db
  .insert(decksTable)
  .values({ userId, name: "Japanese" })
  .returning();
```

## Schema changes

- Add or modify tables only in [src/db/schema.ts](mdc:src/db/schema.ts)
- Generate migrations with `pnpm drizzle-kit generate`
- Apply migrations with `pnpm drizzle-kit migrate`

## Do not

- Use raw SQL (`sql` tagged templates, `db.execute`, direct `neon()` calls) outside [src/db/index.ts](mdc:src/db/index.ts)
- Introduce other ORMs (Prisma, Kysely, TypeORM, etc.)
- Create additional database clients or connection pools elsewhere
- Query tables not defined in the Drizzle schema
